{title: God put a rainbow in the Clouds}
{artist: Chuck Wagon Gang}
{composer: Written by Andrew Jenkins and Irene Spain}

[G]When God shut Noah in the grand old [C]ark
[G]He put a [D7]rainbow in the [G]cloud
When thunders rolled and the sky was [C]dark
[G]God put a [D7]rainbow in the [G]cloud
God put a [C]rainbow in the [G]cloud
[C]God put a rainbow in the [G]cloud
Well it looked like the [G7]sun wouldn't [C]shine any[G]more
God put a [D7]rainbow in the [G]cloud
Away down yonder in Egypt's [C]sand
[G]God put a [D7]rainbow in the [G]cloud
Just to lead his children to the promised [C]land
[G]God put a [D7]rainbow in the [G]cloud
repeat #2

Oh Jordan deep and Jordan [C]wide
[G]God put a [D7]rainbow in the [G]cloud
To lead His people to the other [C]side
[G]God put a [D7]rainbow in the [G]cloud
repeat #2